HIV Prevalence in Phalombe

For a detailed methodology on how these maps were created, please refer to the supplementary material.

District Map

The following interactive map shows HIV prevalence estimates across Phalombe at the district, traditional authority, and 1x1km pixel levels. Health facility locations and details are also shown.

Traditional authorities

The following table lists HIV prevalence among 15 to 49-year olds and population across the same age range for all traditional authorities in Phalombe.

Traditional Authority HIV Prevalence Viral load suppression HIV viraemia
Chiwalo 8.6% (4.5 to 15.0%) 90.6% (78.1 to 97.7%) 0.8% (0.2 to 2.2%)
Jenala 9.1% (5.0 to 15.2%) 91.5% (79.8 to 97.7%) 0.8% (0.2 to 2.0%)
Kaduya 9.2% (5.1 to 14.7%) 91.9% (80.2 to 97.9%) 0.7% (0.2 to 2.1%)
Mkhumba 8.5% (4.7 to 13.9%) 91.6% (80.0 to 97.8%) 0.7% (0.2 to 2.0%)
Nazombe 10.2% (5.6 to 16.6%) 92.0% (80.1 to 98.0%) 0.8% (0.2 to 2.2%)
Nkhulambe 11.3% (6.2 to 18.5%) 93.3% (82.8 to 98.4%) 0.8% (0.2 to 2.3%)
Phalombe Boma 9.3% (4.9 to 15.5%) 91.3% (78.7 to 97.8%) 0.8% (0.2 to 2.1%)
